Cyprus to Cut Civil Servant Wages Up to 2%, Simerini Reports

-- B y   S t e l i o s   O r p h a n i d e s
-- 
2011-05-24T08:03:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/cyprus-to-cut-civil-servant-wages-up-to-2-simerini-reports.html
Cyprus’s government has proposed
cutting civil servants’ pay as much as 2 percent to curb the
public payroll,  Simerini  reported, without saying where it got
the information.  According to a proposal by President Demetris Christofias
to unions,earners of as much as 1,500 euros ($2,113) a month
will take no pay cut, while higher salaries will be reduced by
as much as 2 percent, the Nicosia-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stelios Orphanides in Nicosia at  sorphanides@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at   cstirling1@bloomberg.net  